[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Pagebanner default.jpg"],["pgname=Glacier National Park"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.pc.gc.ca\/pn-np\/bc\/glacier\/index_E.asp Glacier National Park"]}]}," is in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Columbia-Rockies"]]}," region of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Canada"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["History"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Landscape"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Flora and fauna"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Climate"]},"\nThe park lays in the ",{"type":"''","value":["Interior Wetbelt"]}," region of British Columbia which makes for large amounts of precipitation. Mean annual precipitation is 1278mm (50in) at lower elevations and 1995mm (79in) in the subalpine zone. Rogers Pass can see up to an incredible 17 metres of snow each year.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\nAbout the only way into the park is on the Trans-Canada highway 1, which bisects the park. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Calgary"]]}," is about four hours east, and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kamloops"]]}," is about three hours west.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Fees\/Permits"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rogers Pass"]}," - Located at the summit of the park at 1382M (4,534F). The pass' namesake, Major A.B. Rogers was tasked by the Canadian Pacific Railway to find a route through the Selkirk Mountains to bypass the railway's then current ",{"type":"''","value":["Big Bend"]}," alignment. After finding the pass (with the help of native guides) Rogers was presented with a cheque for 5000 dollars, a handsome prize for the times. After Rogers framed the check rather than cashing it, the CPR drew him a new one (and insisted he cash it).  "]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Lodging"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Camping"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Backcountry"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Stay safe"]},"\n\nBecause of the huge amounts of snow, there is a near constant avalanche danger during winter months. There is an online ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.pc.gc.ca\/apps\/psb\/index_E.asp?oqava_park_id=3 avalanche bulletin"]}]}," available.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Head east to visit ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yoho National Park"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Banff National Park"]]},", and further on to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Calgary"]]},".  "]},{"type":"*","value":[" Head west to visit ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Revelstoke"]]},", the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Shuswap"]]},", and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kamloops"]]},"."]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["routebox"],["image1=TCH-1 (BC).svg"],["imagesize1=22"],["directionl1=W"],["majorl1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kamloops"]]}],["minorl1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Revelstoke"]]}],["directionr1=E"],["majorr1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Banff"]]}],["minorr1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Golden (British Columbia)"],["Golden"]]}]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlinepark"]]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["51.3000"],["-117.5186"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["isPartOf"],["Columbia-Rockies"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wikipedia:Glacier National Park (Canada)"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Commons:Category:Glacier National Park (Canada)"]]}]